sub_questions: What features best predict biogas generation?
How do animal types and counts affect biogas output?
What is the relationship between waste efficiency and biogas generation?
How does digester type influence biogas production?
What impact do operational years have on biogas estimates?

schema_conflicts: test.csv has 28 columns while veri_seti_son_2.csv has 29 columns (missing target column)
test.csv missing 'Biogas Generation Estimate (cu-ft/day)' column needed for training

unit_annotations.Biogas_per_Animal (cu-ft/day): cubic feet per day per animal
unit_annotations.Total Emission Reductions (MTCO2e/yr): metric tons CO2 equivalent per year
unit_annotations.Emission_Reduction_per_Year: MTCO2e per year per operational year

scale_issues: Large range in animal counts (120 to 500,000)
Electricity Generated ranges from 0 to 16,206,000 kWh/yr
cross_source_conflicts: test.csv has 74 rows for prediction, veri_seti_son_2.csv has 417 rows for training

format_notes: Quoted strings in Project Name column
Mixed case column names with spaces and special characters
Some columns contain multiple values separated by semicolons (e.g., Biogas End Use(s))

constraints: Biogas Generation Estimate must be positive
Operational Years = Current Year - Year Operational
Biogas_per_Animal = Biogas Generation Estimate / Total_Animals (when both available)
derived_filters: Consider operational status for prediction relevance
Check for data completeness in key predictor columns
statistical_tests: Correlation analysis between biogas generation and animal counts
ANOVA for biogas generation across digester types
Regression analysis for waste efficiency vs biogas output
output_format_requirements: Predictions must be saved in result.csv
One prediction per row in test.csv
